rmat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20that%20quantity%20has%20a%20quality%20of%20its%20own%20and%20that%20it%20isn't%20enough%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20most%20exquisite%20weapons.%3Cp%3EMuhammed%20Enes%20Yildirim%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20is%20teaching%20Western%20militaries%20a%20big%20lesson.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20West%20has%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20focused%20on%20super%20high%20quality%20gear%20over%20sheer%20volume.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20it%20needs%20to%20invest%20more%20in%20quantity%20if%20it%20wants%20to%20defend%20against%20Russia%2C%20warfare%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvasion%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20showing%20the%20West%20the%20value%20of%20quantity%20over%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West%2C%20over%20the%20past%20decades%2C%20has%20focused%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20military%20equipment%20over%20stockpiles%2C%20prioritizing%20high-tech%20and%20specialized%20gear%20over%20sheer%20volume.%20But%20as%20the%20saying%20goes%2C%20quantity%20has%20a%20quality%20of%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20have%20not%20been%20stockpiling%20weapons%20for%20this%20kind%20of%20long-duration%20conflict%2C%20which%2C%20to%20be%20frank%2C%20Russia%20and%20China%20have%20been%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20former%20Australian%20Army%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Mick%20Ryan%2C%20a%20warfare%20strategist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20the%20West%20is%20not%20prepared%20for%20a%20large-scale%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270c5b1db-2e93-4a7b-a8d2-91b114a10a29%5C%22%3EThe%20Western%20approach%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20reacted%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20huge%20mass%20of%20weapory%20last%20century%20with%20the%20mindset%20that%20since%20%26quot%3Bwe%20can't%20achieve%20the%20same%20level%20of%20mass.%20We're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20have%20more%20technologically%20sophisticated%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20George%20Barros%2C%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%2C%20said.%20That%20thinking%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20where%20the%20Abrams%20tank%20came%20from%3A%20a%20search%20for%20heavily%20armored%20firepower%20rather%20than%20mass-produced%20Soviet%20T-series%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20Western%20stockpiles%20of%20weaponry%20diminished%20and%20industry%20shrunk%2C%20leaving%20it%20less%20prepared%20to%20build%20large%20quantities%20of%20munitions%20and%20equipment.%20NATO%20defense%20spending%20has%20largely%20dropped%20while%20China%20and%20Russia%20spend%20increasingly%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West's%20approach%20proved%20successful%20in%20recent%20conflicts%2C%20but%20these%20weren't%20great%20power%20conflicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20American%20military%20wants%20to%20go%20out%20and%20win%20fast%2C%20and%20our%20modern%20image%20of%20the%20preferred%20kind%20of%20war%20is%20sort%20of%20Operation%20Desert%20Storm%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EO'Hanlon%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20and%20the%20director%20of%20research%20in%20the%20foreign%20policy%20program%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20wars%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20whole%20point%20is%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20be%20slogging%20it%20out%20for%20months%20and%20years%20on%20end.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20you%20expect%20to%20be%20successful%20and%20fast%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20sort%20of%20like%20a%20football%20team%20planning%20to%20go%20out%20and%20score%20four%20touchdowns%20in%20the%20first%20half%20just%20to%20end%20the%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20thinking%20like%20that%20leads%20to%20war%20planning%20around%20a%20framework%20that%20no%20longer%20prioritizes%20surge%20capacity%20and%20replenishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20got%20lazy%2C%26quot%3B%20Barros%20said.%20%26quot%3BSure%2C%20you%20have%20better%20equipment%2C%20but%20it's%20horrifically%20expensive%2C%20and%20you%20therefore%20get%20less%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222cb74bd-fb6e-4ffa-b8e5-a08f0306c6ea%5C%22%3EA%20lesson%20from%20Ukraine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20shown%20in%20Ukraine%20that%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20continue%20a%20grinding%2C%20brutal%20fight%20even%20at%20significant%20cost%2C%20and%20it%20appears%20to%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20tank%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667e89f8d1c84a0eaca89801%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22694%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESmoke%20rises%20from%20a%20Russian%20tank%20destroyed%20by%20Ukrainian%20forces.%3Cp%3EANATOLII%20STEPANOV%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20sort%20of%20protracted%20war%2C%20like%20it%20could%20be%20with%20Russia%2C%20%26quot%3Byour%20ability%20to%20sustain%20and%20protract%20the%20war%20actually%20becomes%20key%2C%26quot%3B%20Barros%20said.%20In%20that%20situation%2C%20having%20systems%20that%20might%20not%20be%20as%20good%20but%20that%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20actually%20what's%20going%20to%20make%20the%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West%2C%20he%20said%2C%20can't%20rely%20solely%20on%20big-ticket%20items%20%26quot%3Bunless%20you%20have%20a%20very%20decisive%20war%20immediately%20right%20out%20the%20gate.%26quot%3B%20If%20a%20fight%20isn't%20won%20immediately%2C%20factors%20like%20who%20can%20sustain%20sufficient%20artillery%20fire%20come%20into%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAssuming%20that%20yo